Introduction¶

Dataset Description¶

This dataset collects information from 100k medical appointments in Brazil and is focused on the question of whether or not patients show up for their appointment. A number of characteristics about the patient are included in each row.

‘ScheduledDay’ tells us on what day the patient set up their appointment. ‘AppointmentDay’ tells us on what day the patient he have the appointment. ‘Neighborhood’ indicates the location of the hospital. ‘Scholarship’ indicates whether or not the patient is enrolled in Brasilian welfare program Bolsa Família. ‘No-show’ it says ‘No’ if the patient showed up to their appointment, and ‘Yes’ if they did not show up. list of some diseases [Hipertension, Diabetes, Alcoholism, Handcap]

Question(s) for Analysis¶

Independent

  1. What is ratio between the people who attend in the time and the others ??
  2. The most common day that the people booked ??
  3. The most common day that the people have the appointment ??
  4. The retio between the people who have the scholarship or have not ??
  5. The retio between the people who have the hipertension or have not ??
  6. The retio between the people who have the diabetes or have not ??
  7. The retio between the people who have the alcoholism or have not ??
Dependent
  1. What is ratio between the people who attend in the time and the others depend on gender ??
  2. What is ratio between the people who attend in the time and the others depend on scholarship ??
  3. What is ratio between the people who attend in the time and the others depend on hipertension ??
  4. What is ratio between the people who attend in the time and the others depend on diabetes ??
  5. What is ratio between the people who attend in the time and the others depend on alcoholism ??
  6. What is ratio between the people who over 40 years and under 40 years depend on attendance ??
  7. The most common neighbourhood depend on attendance??

Research Question 9 (What is ratio between the people who have over and under 40 ??)¶

Create new columns and consist of who is over 40 years and who under this age

In [14]:
def new_age_column(df):
    """
    Add new column.

    This function simply just add one column for know that 
    this patient over 40 years old or under 40 years old

    Parameters
    ----------
    df : Data Frame
        The dataset that the function will insert in it.

    Returns
    -------
    Data Frame
        The new dataset with the new column.

    """
    df['Age Category'] = 'Over 40'
    df.loc[df['Age'] < 40, 'Age Category'] = 'Under 40'
new_age_column(df)

Conclusions¶

Finally, this is what we can extract from our dataset

  • The patients that have attend in thier appointment is 79.8% from the dataset
  • The patients that have the scholarship is 9.8% from the dataset
  • The patients that are under the 40 is 53.6 in the dataset
  • The patients that are under the 40 they attend in thier appointment
  • The patients that have not the scholarship most likely that The patients that have the scholarship attend in thier appointment
